<paragraph blockId="5.[151,590,1802,1829]" box="[151,590,1802,1829]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,590,1802,1829]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,590,1802,1829]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[207,478,1802,1829]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,478,1802,1829]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Talorchestia martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
problem
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1875,2045]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,153,1332]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicName authority="(Weber, 1892)" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1892" baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[151,577,1875,1901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[151,405,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Talorchestia martensii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, M." box="[421,568,1875,1901]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" pagination="528 - 571" refId="ref19153" refString="Weber, M. (1892) Der Susswasser-Crustaceen des Indischen Archipels, nebst bemerkungen uber die Susswasser-Fauna im Allgemeinen. Zoologische Ergebnisse einer Reise in Niederlandisch Ost-Indien, 2, 528 - 571, 30 pls., 22 figs." type="book chapter" year="1892">Weber, 1892</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from the south-western coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1249,1319,1875,1901]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Flores</collectingCountry>
in the Indonesian archipelago. Only the gnathopods were illustrated. Based on this description and comparison with other species in the paper it is possible to identify the species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[930,1068,1947,1973]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[930,1068,1947,1973]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Talorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is not possible to identify the species except from the 
<typeStatus box="[459,507,1983,2009]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">type</typeStatus>
locality. Nonetheless 
<bibRefCitation author="Chilton, C." box="[752,916,1983,2009]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" pagination="521 - 558" refId="ref15301" refString="Chilton, C. (1921) Amphipoda. Memoirs of the Indian Museum, 5, 521 - 558." type="journal article" year="1921">Chilton (1921)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1022,1155,1984,2009]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1022,1155,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Chilka Lake, 
<collectingCountry box="[1372,1433,1983,2009]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">India</collectingCountry>
. Based on his detailed description and illustrations the taxon appears to be an undescribed species described below as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[183,321,153,179]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[183,321,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. He subsequently reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[670,805,154,179]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[670,805,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Talé Sap, 
<collectingCountry box="[991,1093,153,179]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, but without description or illustrations. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely, F. H." box="[283,457,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="123 - 124" refId="ref15771" refString="Gravely, F. H. (1927) The littoral fauna of Krusadai Island in the Gulf of Mannar. Bulletin of the Madras Government Museum, 1 (1), 123 - 124." type="journal article" year="1927">Gravely (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, K.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, K. H." box="[532,705,188,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="279 - 319" refId="ref14788" refString="Barnard, K. H. (1935) Report on some Amphipoda, Isopoda, and Tanaidacea in the collections of the Indian Museum. Records of the Indian Museum, 37, 279 - 319, 21 figs." type="book chapter" year="1935">Barnard (1935)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nayar, K. N." box="[761,906,188,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref17706" refString="Nayar, K. N. (1959) The Amphipoda of the Madras Coast. Bulletin of the Madras Government Museum, Natural History Section, 6 (3), 1 - 59, 16 pls." type="book chapter" year="1959">Nayar (1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nayar, K. N." box="[917,974,189,216]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="133 - 168" refId="ref17745" refString="Nayar, K. N. (1967) On the gammaridean Amphipoda of the Gulf of Mannar [sic], with special reference to those of the pearl and chank beds. Proceedings of the Symposium on Crustacea, Ernakulam, 1, 133 - 168, 17 figs." type="book chapter" year="1967">1967</bibRefCitation>
) then reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1148,1284,189,215]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1148,1164,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1178,1284,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from various locations in 
<collectingCountry box="[291,351,225,251]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">India</collectingCountry>
, also without descriptions or illustrations except 
<bibRefCitation author="Nayar, K. N." box="[910,1062,225,252]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="133 - 168" refId="ref17745" refString="Nayar, K. N. (1967) On the gammaridean Amphipoda of the Gulf of Mannar [sic], with special reference to those of the pearl and chank beds. Proceedings of the Symposium on Crustacea, Ernakulam, 1, 133 - 168, 17 figs." type="book chapter" year="1967">Nayar (1967)</bibRefCitation>
who gave simple illustrations of the gnathopods.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="357" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,153,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
<bibRefCitation author="Ruffo, S." box="[199,337,297,323]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="152 - 180" refId="ref18310" refString="Ruffo, S. (1938) Studi sui Crostacei Anfipodi. IX. Gli anfipodi marini del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Gli anfipodi del Mar Rosso. Annali del Museo civico di storia naturale Giacomo Doria, 60, 152 - 180." type="journal article" year="1938">Ruffo (1938</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruffo, S." box="[347,404,297,324]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref18413" refString="Ruffo, S. (1969) Studi sui Crostacei Anfipodi LXVII terzo contributo alla conoscenza degli Anfipodi del Mar Rosso. Memorie del Museo civico di storia naturale di Verona, 17, 1 - 77, 24 figs." type="book chapter" year="1969">1969</bibRefCitation>
) reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[516,648,298,323]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[516,648,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Red Sea without description or illustrations. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruffo, S." box="[1241,1386,297,323]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="205 - 217" refId="ref18358" refString="Ruffo, S. (1948) Studi sui crostacei anfipodi XVII. Gli anfipodi del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova anfipodi Oi Sumatra, Celebes, Nuova Guinea, Australia e Tasmania. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 63, 205 - 217, 3 figs." type="book chapter" year="1948">Ruffo (1948)</bibRefCitation>
also had material from Simatobe, on the south coast of Sumatra. At this time Ruffo synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Maccagno, 1936" authorityName="Maccagno" authorityYear="1936" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franchetti">
<emphasis box="[1183,1436,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia franchetti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maccagno, T. P." box="[151,338,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="171 - 186" refId="ref17060" refString="Maccagno, T. P. (1936) Crostacci di Assab. Decapodi; Stomatopadi, Anfipodi, Spediz. R. Franchetti in Dancalia (1928 - 1929). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 59, 171 - 186." type="journal article" year="1936">Maccagno, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Maccagno, 1936" authorityName="Maccagno" authorityYear="1936" box="[392,683,369,395]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[392,489,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. affinis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maccagno, T. P." box="[496,683,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="171 - 186" refId="ref17060" refString="Maccagno, T. P. (1936) Crostacci di Assab. Decapodi; Stomatopadi, Anfipodi, Spediz. R. Franchetti in Dancalia (1928 - 1929). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 59, 171 - 186." type="journal article" year="1936">Maccagno, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[746,880,370,395]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[746,880,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which extended its range into East Africa and the Red Sea. Neither species had been adequately described. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruffo, S." box="[787,932,405,432]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref18413" refString="Ruffo, S. (1969) Studi sui Crostacei Anfipodi LXVII terzo contributo alla conoscenza degli Anfipodi del Mar Rosso. Memorie del Museo civico di storia naturale di Verona, 17, 1 - 77, 24 figs." type="book chapter" year="1969">Ruffo (1969)</bibRefCitation>
published a map showing a wide distribution for the species in the Indian Ocean, still not illustrated or described. In the 1960’s, a number of experiments were carried out in the equatorial zone of East Africa in 
<collectingCountry box="[716,808,477,503]" name="Somalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Somalia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[862,935,477,503]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Kenya</collectingCountry>
using the amphipod ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1178,1429,477,503]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1178,1429,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ (based on the determination of Ruffo), and aimed mainly at demonstrating the use of the sun as an orienting factor (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A." box="[204,453,549,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="139 - 160" refId="ref17977" refString="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A. (1986) Zonal recovery mechanisms in talitrid crustaceans. Bollettino di Zoologia, 53, 139 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11250008609355499" type="journal article" year="1986">Pardi &amp; Ercolini 1986</bibRefCitation>
for a review). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ercolini, A." box="[621,799,549,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="119 - 128" refId="ref15620" refString="Ercolini, A. (1964 a) Ricerche sull'orientamento astronomico di anfipodi litorali della zona equatoriale. IV. Compensazione differenziale giornaliera del moto azimutale del sole in una popolazione somala di Talorchestia martensii Weber. Zeitschrift fur Vergleichende Physiologie, 49 (2), 119 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02433849" type="journal article" year="1964">
Ercolini (1964 
<bibRefCitation author="Ercolini, A." box="[786,799,549,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="138 - 171" refId="ref15682" refString="Ercolini, A. (1964 b) Ricerche sull'orientamento astronomico di anfipodi litorali della zona equatoriale. I. l'orientamento solare in una popolazione somala di Talorchestia martensii Weber. Zeitschrift fur Vergleichende Physiologie, 49 (2), 138 - 171. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02433849" type="journal article" year="1964">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1964b), 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A." box="[905,1157,549,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="80 - 101" refId="ref17910" refString="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A. (1966) Ricerche sull'orientamento astronomico di anfipodi litorali della zona equatoriale. III. L'orientamento solare in una popolazione di Talorchestia martensi Weber a sud dell'equatore (4 ° Lat. S.). Monitore zoologico italiano, Supplemento, 74, 80 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03749444.1966.10736740" type="journal article" year="1966">Pardi &amp; Ercolini 1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L." box="[1169,1302,549,575]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="44 - 65" refId="ref17878" refString="Pardi, L. (1967) Studi sull'orientamento astronomico dei crostacei anfipodi in regioni equatoriali. Atti dell'Accademia Nazionale Italiana di Entomologia, Rendiconti, 14, 44 - 65." type="journal article" year="1967">Pardi, 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A. &amp; Ferrara, F. &amp; Scapini, F. &amp; Ugolini, A." pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="312 - 320" refId="ref18016" refString="Pardi, L., Ercolini, A., Ferrara, F., Scapini, F. &amp; Ugolini, A. (1984) Orientamento solare e magnetico in Crostacei Anfipodi litorali di regioni equatoriali. Atti della Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei. Rendiconti della Classe di Scienze Fisiche Matematiche e Naturali, Series VIII, 76, 5, 312 - 320." type="journal article" year="1984">
Pardi 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">et al</emphasis>
. 1984
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ugolini, A. &amp; Faqi, A. S. &amp; Scapini, F. &amp; Ercolini, A." box="[262,448,585,611]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="79 - 92" refId="ref18083" refString="Pardi, L., Ugolini, A., Faqi, A. S., Scapini, F. &amp; Ercolini, A. (1988) Zonal recovery in equatorial sandhoppers: interaction be- tween magnetic and solar orientation. In: Chelazzi, G. &amp; Vannini, M. (Eds.), Behavioral Adaptations to Intertidal Life. Plenum, New York, pp. 79 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4899 - 3737 - 7 _ 7" type="book chapter" year="1988">
Pardi 
<emphasis box="[328,378,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">et al</emphasis>
. 1988
</bibRefCitation>
studied talitrid behavior in 
<collectingCountry box="[759,854,585,611]" name="Somalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Somalia</collectingCountry>
. Ruffo identified their study animals as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1303,1436,586,611]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1303,1436,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Scapini pers. comm.). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ugolini, A." box="[484,651,621,647]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="193 - 199" refId="ref18992" refString="Ugolini, A. (2001) Relationship between compass systems of orientation in equatorial Sandhoppers. Animal Behaviour, 62, 193 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.1006 / anbe. 2001.1766" type="journal article" year="2001">Ugolini (2001)</bibRefCitation>
working in 
<collectingCountry box="[787,863,621,647]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, followed suit. We examined some of this material, but only females were available in the collections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,153,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M." box="[199,368,693,719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="250 - 296" refId="ref16156" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1968) Amphipodes Gammariens de quelques biotopes de substrat meuble de la region de Tulear. Etude Systematique et Ecologique. Annales de I ' Universite de Madagascar, 250 - 296." type="book chapter" year="1968">Ledoyer (1968</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M." box="[381,438,693,720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="599 - 1112" refId="ref16252" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1986) Crustaces amphipodes gammariens. Faune de Madagascar, 59 (2), 599 - 1112, figs 227 - 415." type="journal article" year="1986">1986</bibRefCitation>
) then reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[613,747,694,719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[613,747,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Nosy Vé, south-western 
<collectingCountry box="[1098,1235,693,719]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. Based on his description and illustrations it appears he had a new species described below as 
<taxonomicName authority="Lowry &amp; Springthorpe, 2019" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Springthorpe" authorityYear="2019" box="[1038,1266,729,755]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anakao" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1038,1266,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia anakao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1275,1366,729,755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1275,1366,729,755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, D. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="357" refId="ref16079" refString="Jones, D. A. (1986) A Field Guide to the Sea Shores of Kuwait and the Arabian Gulf. Universty of Kuwait, Distributed Blandford Press, Kuwait City, 192 pp." type="book" year="1986">Jones (1986)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[335,469,766,791]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[335,469,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[539,621,765,791]" name="Kuwait" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
in the northern Persian Gulf. If his figure is accurate then the taxon has robust setae on the exopod of uropod 1 and cannot be a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[773,911,801,827]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[773,911,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lyla, P. S. &amp; Velvizhi, S. &amp; Ajmal Khan, S." box="[925,1119,801,827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" refId="ref17016" refString="Lyla, P. S., Velvizhi, S. &amp; Ajmal Khan, S. (1998) Brackish water amphipods of the Parangipettai coast. Centre of Advanced Study in Marine Biology. Annamalai University, Parangipettai, 80 pp." type="book" year="1998">
Lyla 
<emphasis box="[982,1031,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">et al</emphasis>
. (1998)
</bibRefCitation>
reported ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1235,1368,802,827]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1235,1368,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ from Parangipettai, 
<collectingCountry box="[315,376,837,863]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">India</collectingCountry>
. It is not possible to know the species, but the record establishes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[1127,1265,837,863]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1127,1265,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1363,837,863]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">India</collectingCountry>
in the northern Indian Ocean. 
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H." box="[425,750,873,899]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="169 - 200" refId="ref17148" refString="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H. (1999) Taxonomic studies on the Talitridae (Crustacea, Amphipoda) from Taiwan I. The genera Talorchestia and Sinorchestia n. gen. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 38, 169 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 176289" type="journal article" year="1999">Miyamoto &amp; Morino (1999)</bibRefCitation>
gave a detailed description and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1300,1436,874,899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[441,527,909,935]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Springthorpe, R. T. &amp; Azman B. A. R." box="[537,967,909,935]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="401 - 434" refId="ref16659" refString="Lowry, J. K., Springthorpe, R. T. &amp; Azman B. A. R. (2017) The talitrid amphipod genus Talorchestia from the South China Sea to the Indonesian Archipelago (Crustacea, Senticaudata). Zootaxa, 4319 (3), 401 - 434. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4319.3.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Lowry, Springthorpe &amp; Azman (2017)</bibRefCitation>
accepted the redescription of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1303,1436,910,935]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[1303,1436,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H." box="[187,506,945,971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="169 - 200" refId="ref17148" refString="Miyamoto, H. &amp; Morino, H. (1999) Taxonomic studies on the Talitridae (Crustacea, Amphipoda) from Taiwan I. The genera Talorchestia and Sinorchestia n. gen. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 38, 169 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 176289" type="journal article" year="1999">Miyamoto &amp; Morino (1999)</bibRefCitation>
“until new material from the 
<typeStatus box="[841,889,945,971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">type</typeStatus>
locality is collected and described”. Finally 
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, X." pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="1 - 558" refId="ref18179" refString="Ren, X. (2006) Crustacea Amphipoda Gammaridea (I). Fauna Sinica Invertebrata, 41, i-x, 1 - 558." type="journal article" year="2006">Ren (2006)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[333,467,982,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensii">
<emphasis box="[333,467,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">T. martensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Hainan Island in a table.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,153,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
Recently Baldanzi collected two species of talitrids from Gazi Beach, 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1095,1017,1043]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. Gazi (Maftaha) Bay (
<geoCoordinate box="[1358,1436,1016,1043]" degrees="4" direction="south" minutes="25" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" precision="925" value="-4.4166665">4°25’S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[151,245,1053,1079]" degrees="39" direction="east" minutes="30" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" precision="925" value="39.5">39°30’E</geoCoordinate>
) is a shallow, tropical coastal water system situated in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[996,1072,1053,1079]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, approximately 
<quantity box="[1258,1332,1053,1079]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" unit="km" value="47.0">47 km</quantity>
south of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,261,1089,1115]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Mombasa</collectingCountry>
and near 
<collectingCountry box="[371,463,1089,1115]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Malindi</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[474,547,1089,1115]" name="Kenya" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[564,642,1089,1115]" degrees="3" direction="south" minutes="13" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" precision="925" value="-3.2166667">3°13’S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[648,743,1089,1115]" degrees="40" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" precision="925" value="40.116665">40°07’E</geoCoordinate>
) the site of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ugolini, A." box="[876,1062,1089,1115]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="193 - 199" refId="ref18992" refString="Ugolini, A. (2001) Relationship between compass systems of orientation in equatorial Sandhoppers. Animal Behaviour, 62, 193 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.1006 / anbe. 2001.1766" type="journal article" year="2001">Ugolini’s (2001)</bibRefCitation>
study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,153,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">
In this paper we describe 
<taxonomicName authority="Lowry &amp; Springthorpe, 2019" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Springthorpe" authorityYear="2019" box="[500,623,1125,1151]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Gazia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gazi" status="gen. nov., sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[500,623,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Gazia gazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[633,850,1125,1151]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[633,741,1125,1151]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">gen. nov.</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[757,850,1125,1151]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and describe 
<taxonomicName authority="Maccagno, 1936" authorityName="Maccagno" authorityYear="1936" box="[1012,1432,1125,1151]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[1012,1230,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia affinis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maccagno, T. P." box="[1240,1432,1125,1151]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="171 - 186" refId="ref17060" refString="Maccagno, T. P. (1936) Crostacci di Assab. Decapodi; Stomatopadi, Anfipodi, Spediz. R. Franchetti in Dancalia (1928 - 1929). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 59, 171 - 186." type="journal article" year="1936">Maccagno, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the Baldanzi collections, the collections of Maccagno from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1048,1124,1161,1187]" name="Eritrea" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
and the collections studied by Ruffo from Port 
<collectingCountry box="[376,446,1197,1223]" name="Sudan" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Sudan</collectingCountry>
and Hurghada (as Al Ghardaqa) along the west coast of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1130,1227,1197,1223]" country="Sudan" name="Al Bahr al Ahmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Red Sea</collectingRegion>
. This confirms the records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[268,406,1233,1259]" class="Malacostraca" family="Talitridae" genus="Talorchestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,406,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Talorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from eastern Africa and the 
<collectingRegion box="[719,810,1233,1259]" country="Sudan" name="Al Bahr al Ahmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Red Sea</collectingRegion>
and verifies the distribution of the genus from 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1436,1233,1259]" name="Indonesia" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
to East Africa in the western Indian Ocean. It is almost certainly the same species studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ercolini, A." box="[1214,1393,1269,1295]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="119 - 128" refId="ref15620" refString="Ercolini, A. (1964 a) Ricerche sull'orientamento astronomico di anfipodi litorali della zona equatoriale. IV. Compensazione differenziale giornaliera del moto azimutale del sole in una popolazione somala di Talorchestia martensii Weber. Zeitschrift fur Vergleichende Physiologie, 49 (2), 119 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02433849" type="journal article" year="1964">Ercolini (1964a</bibRefCitation>
, b), 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A." box="[151,420,1305,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="80 - 101" refId="ref17910" refString="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A. (1966) Ricerche sull'orientamento astronomico di anfipodi litorali della zona equatoriale. III. L'orientamento solare in una popolazione di Talorchestia martensi Weber a sud dell'equatore (4 ° Lat. S.). Monitore zoologico italiano, Supplemento, 74, 80 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03749444.1966.10736740" type="journal article" year="1966">Pardi &amp; Ercolini (1966)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L." box="[432,575,1305,1332]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="44 - 65" refId="ref17878" refString="Pardi, L. (1967) Studi sull'orientamento astronomico dei crostacei anfipodi in regioni equatoriali. Atti dell'Accademia Nazionale Italiana di Entomologia, Rendiconti, 14, 44 - 65." type="journal article" year="1967">Pardi (1967)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ercolini, A. &amp; Ferrara, F. &amp; Scapini, F. &amp; Ugolini, A." box="[587,793,1305,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="312 - 320" refId="ref18016" refString="Pardi, L., Ercolini, A., Ferrara, F., Scapini, F. &amp; Ugolini, A. (1984) Orientamento solare e magnetico in Crostacei Anfipodi litorali di regioni equatoriali. Atti della Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei. Rendiconti della Classe di Scienze Fisiche Matematiche e Naturali, Series VIII, 76, 5, 312 - 320." type="journal article" year="1984">
Pardi 
<emphasis box="[653,702,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardi, L. &amp; Ugolini, A. &amp; Faqi, A. S. &amp; Scapini, F. &amp; Ercolini, A." box="[804,1008,1305,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="79 - 92" refId="ref18083" refString="Pardi, L., Ugolini, A., Faqi, A. S., Scapini, F. &amp; Ercolini, A. (1988) Zonal recovery in equatorial sandhoppers: interaction be- tween magnetic and solar orientation. In: Chelazzi, G. &amp; Vannini, M. (Eds.), Behavioral Adaptations to Intertidal Life. Plenum, New York, pp. 79 - 92. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4899 - 3737 - 7 _ 7" type="book chapter" year="1988">
Pardi 
<emphasis box="[870,920,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="357">et al</emphasis>
. (1988)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ugolini, A." box="[1063,1233,1305,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="357" pagination="193 - 199" refId="ref18992" refString="Ugolini, A. (2001) Relationship between compass systems of orientation in equatorial Sandhoppers. Animal Behaviour, 62, 193 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.1006 / anbe. 2001.1766" type="journal article" year="2001">Ugolini (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
